<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B91.I/OHardware.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong=
>1. I/O Hardware</strong></h1>
<p>Hardware is the <strong>physical interface</strong> between the computer=
 and external environment.</p>
<h3 id=3D"OperatingSystem-Components&amp;Details:">Components &amp; Details=
:</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Disk Drives (HDD, SSD):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Store data permanently.</p></li>
<li>
<p>HDD: magnetic storage, mechanical read/write heads =E2=86=92 slower acce=
ss.</p></li>
<li>
<p>SSD: flash memory, faster access, no moving parts.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used for storing programs, files, databases.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Terminals:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Input: Keyboard, mouse, scanners</p></li>
<li>
<p>Output: Monitor, printer</p></li>
<li>
<p>Serve as <strong>user-computer communication points</strong>.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Clocks / Timers:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Provide <strong>synchronization signals</strong> for operations.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Real-time clocks track actual time.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Controllers / Interface Cards:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Bridge hardware and CPU.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Example: USB controller, disk controller.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Translate general commands into device-specific signals.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B92.I/OSoftware.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong=
>2. I/O Software</strong></h1>
<p>Software manages the <strong>interaction between hardware and applicatio=
ns</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"OperatingSystem-Components&amp;Details:.1">Components &amp; Detai=
ls:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Device Drivers:</strong> Programs that control specific hardware=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Buffers / Caches:</strong> Temporarily store data to <strong>smo=
oth out speed differences</strong> between CPU and devices.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>I/O Scheduling / Management:</strong> Determines the order of da=
ta transfers to improve efficiency (important for disks, printers).</p></li=
>
</ul>
<p><strong>Role:</strong> Makes I/O reliable, efficient, and easier for pro=
grams to use without knowing hardware details.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B93.Disks.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>3. Di=
sks</strong></h1>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Structure:</strong> Tracks (concentric circles), sectors (divisi=
ons of tracks), cylinders (aligned tracks across platters).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Performance Factors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Seek time:</strong> Moving the head to the correct track</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><strong>Rotational latency:</strong> Waiting for the sector to rotate un=
der the head</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Transfer time:</strong> Actually reading/writing data</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Role:</strong> Provide large, persistent storage with relatively=
 fast access.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B94.Terminals.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>4=
. Terminals</strong></h1>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Allow <strong>human-computer interaction</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Character-based terminals:</strong> Input/output is text only (k=
eyboard, text screen).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Graphical terminals:</strong> Support GUI (monitor, touchscreen)=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Function:</strong> Collect input from user and display output cl=
early.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B95.Clocks.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>5. C=
locks</strong></h1>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>System Clock:</strong> Generates pulses to synchronize all CPU o=
perations.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Real-Time Clock:</strong> Keeps track of actual time for timesta=
mps, scheduling, alarms.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Function:</strong> Ensures orderly execution of tasks, maintains=
 correct timing for processes and I/O.</p></li>
</ul>
