<ol start=3D"7">
<li>
<p>Deadlock: resource allocation and deadlock, deadlock detection, preventi=
on and recovery;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8D Let=E2=80=99s break this down carefully.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B9DeadlockinOperatingSystems">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 <strong>Deadlock in Operating Systems</strong></h1>
<p>A <strong>deadlock</strong> is a situation in which a set of processes a=
re blocked because each process is holding a resource and waiting for anoth=
er resource held by some other process.<br>
It=E2=80=99s like <strong>two people shaking hands but not letting go until=
 the other does first</strong> =E2=86=92 both stuck forever.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-1.ResourceAllocationandDeadlock">1. <strong>Resou=
rce Allocation and Deadlock</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A system has <strong>resources</strong> (CPU, memory, printers, files, e=
tc.).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Processes request, hold, and release resources.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>A <strong>deadlock</strong> occurs when all of these <strong>four condit=
ions</strong> hold (Coffman=E2=80=99s Conditions):</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Mutual Exclusion:</strong> Resources can=E2=80=99t be shared, on=
ly one process at a time (e.g., a printer).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Hold and Wait:</strong> A process holding at least one resource =
can request more.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>No Preemption:</strong> Resources cannot be forcibly taken away.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Circular Wait:</strong> A closed chain of processes exists, each=
 waiting for a resource held by the next process.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 If all four hold simultaneously =E2=86=92 <strong>deadlock =
can occur</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-2.DeadlockDetection">2. <strong>Deadlock Detectio=
n</strong></h2>
<p>The system checks if a deadlock has happened.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Resource Allocation Graph (RAG):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Processes (P1, P2, =E2=80=A6) and Resources (R1, R2, =E2=80=A6) are draw=
n as nodes.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Edges: Process =E2=86=92 Resource (request), Resource =E2=86=92 Process =
(allocation).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Cycle in RAG =3D Deadlock possible</strong> (if single instance =
per resource).</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Detection Algorithm:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Similar to Banker=E2=80=99s Algorithm.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Check if available resources can satisfy waiting processes.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If not =E2=86=92 Deadlock detected.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>P1 waiting for R2, but R2 held by P2.</p></li>
<li>
<p>P2 waiting for R1, but R1 held by P1.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Cycle =E2=86=92 Deadlock.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-3.DeadlockPrevention">3. <strong>Deadlock Prevent=
ion</strong></h2>
<p>We stop at least <strong>one Coffman condition</strong> from happening.<=
/p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Mutual Exclusion:</strong> Not always preventable (some resource=
s are non-sharable).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Hold and Wait:</strong> Require processes to request all resourc=
es at once.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>No Preemption:</strong> Allow the OS to take resources back.</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Circular Wait:</strong> Impose ordering of resources (e.g., requ=
est in increasing ID order).</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>If printer =3D Resource 1, scanner =3D Resource 2 =E2=86=92 Processes mu=
st always ask for Resource 1 before 2 =E2=86=92 No cycle possible.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-4.DeadlockAvoidance">4. <strong>Deadlock Avoidanc=
e</strong></h2>
<p>Instead of prevention, avoid unsafe states.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Banker=E2=80=99s Algorithm</strong> is commonly used.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Process must declare maximum needs beforehand.</p></li>
<li>
<p>System checks if granting request keeps system in a <strong>safe state</=
strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If yes =E2=86=92 grant. If no =E2=86=92 block.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-5.DeadlockRecovery">5. <strong>Deadlock Recovery<=
/strong></h2>
<p>If deadlock happens =E2=86=92 fix it.</p>
<p>Methods:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Process Termination:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Kill one or more processes until deadlock cycle breaks.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can terminate all deadlocked processes or one at a time.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Resource Preemption:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Take resources away and assign to others.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Must decide:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Which process</strong> to preempt?</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Which resource</strong> to take?</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>How to roll back</strong> the affected process?</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B9SummaryTable.1">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>=
Summary Table</strong></h1>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7a=
9b0f26-b6d0-42ed-89e0-c05dee7305ce" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Method</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Idea</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Detection</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Check for deadlock (graph, algorithms)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>RAG cycle check</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Prevention</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Break one of 4 conditions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Order resources</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Avoidance</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use safe states</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Banker=E2=80=99s Algorithm</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Recovery</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Resolve after it occurs</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Kill process / Preempt</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 Do you want me to also <strong>draw a simple resource alloc=
ation graph example</strong> (with cycle showing deadlock) so it=E2=80=99s =
visually clear?</p>
<p>Great =F0=9F=91=8D Let=E2=80=99s dive into <strong>Banker=E2=80=99s Algo=
rithm</strong>, one of the most important <strong>deadlock avoidance algori=
thms</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 id=3D"OperatingSystem-=F0=9F=94=B9Banker=E2=80=99sAlgorithm">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 <strong>Banker=E2=80=99s Algorithm</strong></h1>
<p>It was proposed by <strong>Edsger Dijkstra</strong>.<br>
The idea: The system works like a banker giving loans =F0=9F=92=B0.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A customer (process) must tell in advance the <strong>maximum resources<=
/strong> it may need.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The banker (OS) gives resources only if it can ensure that <strong>all c=
ustomers can still finish safely</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-1.DataStructuresUsed">1. <strong>Data Structures =
Used</strong></h2>
<p>For <strong>n processes</strong> and <strong>m resources</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Available[m]</strong> =E2=86=92 Number of instances of each reso=
urce currently available.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Max[n][m]</strong> =E2=86=92 Maximum demand of each process.</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Allocation[n][m]</strong> =E2=86=92 Currently allocated resource=
s for each process.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Need[n][m]</strong> =3D Max - Allocation =E2=86=92 Remaining res=
ources a process needs.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"OperatingSystem-2.StepsinBanker=E2=80=99sAlgorithm">2. <strong>St=
eps in Banker=E2=80=99s Algorithm</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"OperatingSystem-(A)SafetyAlgorithm(checkifsystemisinasafestate):"=
>(A) <strong>Safety Algorithm</strong> (check if system is in a safe state)=
:</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Work =3D Available, Finish[i] =3D false for all processes.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Find a process <code>Pi</code> such that:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Need[i] =E2=89=A4 Work</p></li>
<li>
<p>Finish[i] =3D false</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If found:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Work =3D Work + Allocation[i]</p></li>
<li>
<p>Finish[i] =3D true</p></li>
<li>
<p>Repeat step 2</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If all processes finish =E2=86=92 <strong>Safe state</strong>.<br>
Otherwise =E2=86=92 <strong>Unsafe (possible deadlock)</strong>.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"OperatingSystem-(B)ResourceRequestAlgorithm(whenprocessPirequests=
resources):">(B) <strong>Resource Request Algorithm</strong> (when process =
Pi requests resources):</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>If Request[i] =E2=89=A4 Need[i] =E2=86=92 continue. Else =E2=86=92 error=
 (asking more than max).</p></li>
<li>
<p>If Request[i] =E2=89=A4 Available =E2=86=92 continue. Else =E2=86=92 wai=
t (not enough resources).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Pretend to allocate resources:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Available =3D Available =E2=80=93 Request[i]</p></li>
<li>
<p>Allocation[i] =3D Allocation[i] + Request[i]</p></li>
<li>
<p>Need[i] =3D Need[i] =E2=80=93 Request[i]</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Run <strong>safety algorithm</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>If safe =E2=86=92 grant request.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If unsafe =E2=86=92 deny and restore original state.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
